OCI Prices Offer of 1.49 Million Global Depositary Shares at $464 Each

-- B y   S a n g i m   H a n
-- 
2011-05-23T06:35:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/oci-prices-offer-of-1-49-million-global-depositary-shares-at-464-each.html
OCI Co. priced its offering of global
depositary receipts, representing 1.49 million ordinary shares,
at a price of 510,000 won ($464) each, according to its
regulatory filing to the Korea Exchange today.  The offer price is 2.7 percent lower than its closing price
on Friday. Ten GDRs will represent one ordinary share and will
be listed on the Singapore exchange on June 1.  Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN) ,  Barclays Plc (BARC)  and Royal Bank of
Scotland Group arranged the sale.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sangim Han in Seoul at 
 sihan@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Brett Miller at 
 bmiller30@bloomberg.net  